==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Weatherglass
<hw>Weath"er*glass`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>An instrument
to indicate the state of the atmosphere, especially changes of
atmospheric pressure, and hence changes of weather, as a barometer or
baroscope.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Poor man's weatherglass</b></col>. <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<cd>See under <er>Poor</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Weathering</ent>⟦br⟧
